column5: Literally!  Caught on my fly in trip to John's Lake in August. It had a close look at my jig with its GIANT eye and liked what it saw.
The eye is a meal in its self
WOW!!! Mike, that WALL-eye could reach the ceiling, I was floored when I first saw it! Thanks for sharing the pic. I'm a little squeamish  at those sights but this one is ok.
Ive caught a couple with huge tumors as well...... Why is it that they're like the only fish that gets them, and does that affect consumption?
They're evolving towards having x-ray vision to see anglers' hooks  That's what walleyes of the future will look like
An eye for an eye a fish for a fry
I've seen that a few times too.......right after I bonk them on the head LOL  S.
Man, right before turkey dinner. I might only have 3 plates.
LMAO Rob.  Check out Doug,s Erie eyes. There,s some bugged out eyes there too.
Eye am amazed at that eye's eye! Your hookset probably knocked off his eyeglasses...
I'm guessing you let that one go, it doesn't look overly appetizing
